  "notes": [
    "UI mode is HEADLESS — the script has no ScriptUI dialog; screenshot and uiTree are null.",
    "All five expression curves are identity/pass-through functions (y = x): each expression is a direct effect control lookup that returns exactly the value set on the control.",
    "Fill Color and Stroke Color curves sweep one color channel component over [0, 1]; in AE these controls return RGBA arrays, but the sim sweeps a single channel component for visualization.",
    "Fill Opacity and Stroke Opacity curves sweep the slider over [0, 100], producing a linear ramp (0% transparent to 100% opaque).",
    "Stroke Width curve sweeps the slider over [0, 50 px], producing a linear ramp from 0 to 50 px; default control value is 5 px."
  ]
}
